### [Daniel Chapter 7](../../../bib/kjv/dan007.htm#001.md)

[Daniel 7:2](../../../bib/kjv/dan007.htm#002.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_002">dan 7:2</span></span>

great sea

The "sea" in Scripture imagery stands for the populace, the mere
unorganized mass of mankind ([Mat
13:47](../../../bib/kjv/mat013.htm#047).md); ([Rev
13:1](../../../bib/kjv/rev013.htm#001).md).

[Daniel 7:5](../../../bib/kjv/dan007.htm#005.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_005">dan 7:5</span></span>

three ribs

A reference to the three-fold dominion of the second empire, Media,
Persia, Babylonia.

devour

That is, Lydia, Babylonia, Egypt, etc.

[Daniel 7:6](../../../bib/kjv/dan007.htm#006.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_006">dan 7:6</span></span>

leopard

Swiftness of Alexander's conquests.

[Daniel 7:7](../../../bib/kjv/dan007.htm#007.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_007">dan 7:7</span></span>

horns

A horn symbolizes a king.

Compare ([Rev 17:12](../../../bib/kjv/rev017.htm#012).md).

[Daniel 7:8](../../../bib/kjv/dan007.htm#008.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_008">dan 7:8</span></span>

little horn

The vision is of the end of Gentile world-dominion. The former Roman
empire (the iron kingdom of ([Dan
2:33-35](../../../bib/kjv/dan002.htm#033).md); ([Dan
2:40-44](../../../bib/kjv/dan002.htm#040).md); ([Dan
7:7](../../../bib/kjv/dan007.htm#007).md) will have ten horns (that is,
kings, ([Rev 17:12](../../../bib/kjv/rev017.htm#012).md) corresponding to
the ten toes of the image. As Daniel considers this vision of the ten
kings, there rises up amongst them a "little horn" (king), who subdues
three of the ten kings so completely that the separate identity of their
kingdoms is destroyed.

Seven kings of the ten are left, and the "little horn." He is the "king
of fierce countenance" typified by that other "king of fierce
countenance," Antiochus Epiphanes, ([Dan
8:23-25](../../../bib/kjv/dan008.htm#023).md) the "prince that shall come"
of ([Dan 9:26](../../../bib/kjv/dan009.htm#026).md); ([Dan
9:27](../../../bib/kjv/dan009.htm#027).md) the "king" of ([Dan
11:36-45](../../../bib/kjv/dan011.htm#036).md) the "abomination" of; ([Dan
12:11](../../../bib/kjv/dan012.htm#011).md); ([Mat
24:15](../../../bib/kjv/mat024.htm#015).md) the "man of sin" of ([Th2
2:4-8](../../../bib/kjv/th2002.htm#004).md) and the "Beast" of ([Rev
13:4-10](../../../bib/kjv/rev013.htm#004).md).

See "Beast"; ([Dan 7:8](../../../bib/kjv/dan007.htm#008).md); ([Rev
19:20](../../../bib/kjv/rev019.htm#020).md).

[Daniel 7:13](../../../bib/kjv/dan007.htm#013.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_013">dan 7:13</span></span>

and they

This scene is identical with that of ([Rev
5:6-10](../../../bib/kjv/rev005.htm#006).md). There the ascription of
praise of the "kings and priests" (Compare ([Dan
7:18](../../../bib/kjv/dan007.htm#018).md); ([Dan
7:18](../../../bib/kjv/dan007.htm#018)); ref. A.md) ends with the words,
"and we shall reign on the earth." Revelation 6. opens the "vexing" of
([Psa 2:5](../../../bib/kjv/psa002.htm#005).md) introductory to setting the
king on Zion; ([Psa 2:6](../../../bib/kjv/psa002.htm#006).md); ([Rev
20:4](../../../bib/kjv/rev020.htm#004).md). The vision ([Dan
7:9-14](../../../bib/kjv/dan007.htm#009).md) reverses the order of events
as they will be fulfilled. Verse 13 ([Dan
7:13](../../../bib/kjv/dan007.htm#013).md) describes the scene in heaven
(cf) ([Rev 5:6-10](../../../bib/kjv/rev005.htm#006).md) which, in
fulfilment, precedes the events which Daniel sees in vision in ([Dan
7:9-12](../../../bib/kjv/dan007.htm#009).md). The historic order will be:

\(1\) The investiture of the Son of Man with the kingdom ([Dan
7:13](../../../bib/kjv/dan007.htm#013).md); ([Dan
7:14](../../../bib/kjv/dan007.htm#014).md); ([Rev
5:6-10](../../../bib/kjv/rev005.htm#006).md).

\(2\) the "vexing" of ([Psa 2:5](../../../bib/kjv/psa002.htm#005).md);
fully described in ([Mat 24:21](../../../bib/kjv/mat024.htm#021).md); ([Mat
24:22](../../../bib/kjv/mat024.htm#022).md) Revelation 6-18.

\(3\) The return of the Son of Man in glory to deliver the "smiting"
blow of ([Dan 2:45](../../../bib/kjv/dan002.htm#045).md); ([Dan
7:9-11](../../../bib/kjv/dan007.htm#009).md); ([Rev
19:11-21](../../../bib/kjv/rev019.htm#011).md).

\(4\) The judgement of the nations and the setting up of the kingdom
([Dan 7:10](../../../bib/kjv/dan007.htm#010).md); ([Dan
7:26](../../../bib/kjv/dan007.htm#026).md); ([Dan
7:27](../../../bib/kjv/dan007.htm#027).md); ([Mat
25:31-46](../../../bib/kjv/mat025.htm#031).md); ([Rev
20:1-6](../../../bib/kjv/rev020.htm#001).md).

